Explanation:

1. Sort both arrays (event1 and event2) using the `Arrays.sort()` method to ensure consistent comparison.
2. Iterate through event1 and event2 using nested loops.
3. Compare each element of event1 with all elements of event2. If a match is found, return true, indicating a conflict.
4. If no conflict is found after checking all elements, return false, indicating no conflict.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n^2) because of the nested loops, where n is the number of elements in event1 and event2. The space complexity is O(n) due to the usage of the `Arrays.sort()` method and the arrays themselves. The energy implications are low because the solution only involves simple comparisons and does not require any intensive operations.

